Script,FinesseSimple
window.currentPBSScenario = 'FinesseSimple';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Finesse_Simple';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for FinesseSimple');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'FinesseSimple',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: 21GF-DEFAULT
convention-card-ew: 21GF-GIB
auction-filter: Auction.....\n1S +Pass +3S +Pass\n4S
*/
# ----- South opens 1S -----
# 5 or 6 spades headed by AK, exactly 3 hearts headed by AQ (no K),
# 14-17 HCP. No second 5-card suit so the auction stays 1S.
sSpadesLen = spades(south) == 5 or spades(south) == 6
sSpadeTop  = top2(south, spades) == 2
sHearts3   = hearts(south) == 3
sHasAQH    = hascard(south, AH) and hascard(south, QH)
sNoKH      = not hascard(south, KH)
sHcp       = hcp(south) > 13 and hcp(south) < 18
sNoSide5   = diamonds(south) < 5 and clubs(south) < 5
oneS = sSpadesLen and sSpadeTop and sHearts3 and sHasAQH and sNoKH and sHcp and sNoSide5

# ----- North limit-raises to 3S -----
# Exactly 3-card spade support, 10-11 HCP, balanced (no 5+ side suit),
# and does NOT hold the heart K (so the finesse is a real choice).
nSpades3   = spades(north) == 3
nHcp       = hcp(north) > 9 and hcp(north) < 12
nNoLong    = hearts(north) < 5 and diamonds(north) < 5 and clubs(north) < 5
nNoKH      = not hascard(north, KH)
limitRaise = nSpades3 and nHcp and nNoLong and nNoKH

##### Imported Script: Define Calm Opponents #####

# Avoid concentration of values
cce = top4(east,clubs)<2
cde = top4(east,diamonds)<2
che = top4(east,hearts)<2
cse = top4(east,spades)<2
noConEast = cce and cde and che and cse

ccw = top4(west,clubs)<2
cdw = top4(west,diamonds)<2
chw = top4(west,hearts)<2
csw = top4(west,spades)<2
noConWest = ccw and cdw and chw and csw

balEast    = shape(east,any 4432 +any 4333)
unbalEast  = shape(east,xxxx -any 4432 -any 4333 -any 9xxx -any 8xxx -any 7xxx-any 6xxx -any 55xx)

balWest    = shape(west,any 4432 +any 4333)
unbalWest  = shape(west,xxxx -any 4432 -any 4333 -any 9xxx -any 8xxx -any 7xxx-any 6xxx -any 55xx)

calmEast = (unbalEast and noConEast and hcp(east)<8) or (balEast and hcp(east)<11)
calmWest = (unbalWest and noConWest and hcp(west)<8) or (balWest and hcp(west)<11)
calmOpps = calmEast and calmWest

##### End of Imported Script: Define Calm Opponents #####
# Returns calmEast, calmWest, calmOpps so neither defender interferes.

# ----- Combine -----
oneS and limitRaise and calmOpps

action printoneline,
average "South 5 spades       " 100 * (spades(south) == 5),
average "South 6 spades       " 100 * (spades(south) == 6),
average "Heart K with East    " 100 * hascard(east, KH),
average "Heart K with West    " 100 * hascard(west, KH),
average "South HCP avg        "       hcp(south),
average "North HCP avg        "       hcp(north),
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Finesse - Simple,\n\
--- Simple Finesse (4!S by South)\n\
South opens 1!S，North gives a limit raise (3!S)，South accepts game (4!S).\n\
\n\
The teaching feature: South holds the ♥A and ♥Q but is missing the ♥K. The K\n\
sits in East or West with roughly equal frequency. A finesse — leading low\n\
from dummy toward South's hand and playing the Q if East follows small —\n\
picks up the suit when East has the K (about half the time).\n\
\n\
Things to think about before touching the heart suit:\n\
• Count winners and losers first.\n\
• Decide when to take the finesse: before or after drawing all trumps?\n\
• If the finesse loses，which side suit will yield the extra trick?\n\
• Did the auction or the opening lead hint where the K sits?\n\
\n\
Reference on the basic finesse: https://www.bridgebum.com/finesse.php\n\
%FinesseSimple%
